metadata.name: Redundancy #121
metadata.description:
This generative token explores redundancy as an architectural concept, method, and process. Redundancy provides flexibility in an open form, enabling a shift from monofunctional to multifunctional as well as from optimized to resilient. A hybrid architecture in which complexity is created through the continuous reconfiguration of simple discrete and compatible blocks.
Each minted redundancy token reveals various deterministic rare features, styles, and scales, creating endlessly redundant open architectures. 

Redundancy Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022

"Opposites are not contradictory but complementary." -¬†Niels Bohr

This idea¬†reverberates through nature, art, and life itself. Now it is at the heart of modern physics. Perhaps this is a fundamental¬†law of nature baked into the¬†very fabric of existence.

Antiflow is an exploration of how balanced complexity can arise¬†from chaos by harnessing the dynamic interplay of opposing¬†forces. To that end we were inspired to create this wildly unique¬†set by mixing modern physics concepts with abstract expressionism and retro 3D primitives.

metadata.name: Fabric Remnants #65
metadata.description:
One of my sisters is a tailor and restorator. This piece is a homage to her. 
Shopping for fabric with her and seeing her atelier while she is working is a 
festival of color, shapes, patterns and a celebration of creativity.

This is my pragmatical take on her work. The fabric like texture and dashed lines
representing the yarn rearranged in a grid of leftovers.

The piece is a generated SVG, because of that it scales easily and is printable.

Use the arrow keys to toggle/tune some things & Space / click to regenerate a new
grid. The P key will toggle auto generation.

metadata.name: Punktwelt #454
metadata.description:
Continuing on the theme of color perception in Farbteiler, Punktwelt is an exploration of color interaction, projection and perceived depth, and the aesthetics of simple Boolean operations on form.

Each shape is the result of a single block, a rectangular cuboid, subjected to a series of Boolean subtractions with other blocks, and rendered in parallel projection, oblique or axonometric, in the abstract landscape of the Punktwelt.

Some have horizons, some have banded or striped backgrounds. The unnatural drawing order and chromatic differences of the individual faces sometimes yields illusory or paradoxical visual geometries.

Press ‚Äôs‚Äô to save a png. Press ‚Äô4‚Äô to export a high resolution png. Press ‚Äô8‚Äô to export a very high resolution png. Press ‚Äôe‚Äô to export an SVG file (may take some time and produce large files).

Aspect ratio variations are 4:5, 5:4, 2:3, 3:2 and 1:1.

Built in Javascript with p5.js, p5.svg and csg.js.

metadata.name: Subatomic Compositions #254
metadata.description:
My love of physics predates my love for generative systems. This piece explores the compositional beauty that can arise from particle collisions in the subatomic space. The aesthetic is based on bubble chamber photography: the paths of particles are traced and photographed as they split and collide.

The primary particle travels at extreme speeds, looping around until it collides with another particle. The resulting explosion is traced out and interesting events are highlighted. Some of the particles shoot off at incredible velocity, and others spiral tighter and tighter until they blink out of existence.

This is a study in composition.

metadata.name: Reblend #16
metadata.description:
There are two creative features to this project.
The first feature is related to the production of colors at random points, so that geometric shapes are placed in proper harmony with each other and then allowed to process and produce colors at the intersection.
The second feature is the subtraction of a part of the shapes that are located in the center, and in the place of subtraction, geometric shapes are replaced, which will produce a new content of regular geometric shapes.
This innovative art not only challenges the traditional concepts of beauty but also encourages the thinking of viewers to combine colors and geometric shapes.

S = Save
Made by p5.js

metadata.name: Hasir #38
metadata.description:
Do you want to build a mat wall that is strong?
I looked at the basic structure of modern architectural structures and combined them with traditional structures.
I placed a cube in a 3D space which is displayed from different angles. Then, using CSG.js, I randomly created empty spaces inside this cube. I created the walls from mats so that the inside of the work can be seen through them, so it is easy to feel the depths and directions.

Made by, p5.js - CSG.js

metadata.name: Pixel Plus #111
metadata.description:
I took inspiration from retro video games and pixel art in this style but added a modern twist by incorporating intricate details and designs.
I separated and carefully arranged the pixels to form intricate patterns, shapes, and images. And I gave the effect a distinctly retro feel by using limited colors and blocky pixels to create creativity and imagination.
The result is a visually striking piece that captures the viewer's attention with bold colors, sharp edges, and meticulous attention to detail. Each pixel is carefully placed to create depth and texture, resulting in a nostalgic and contemporary work of art.
Made by p5.js

metadata.name: SoulFish #110
metadata.description:
Named after the artist Wu Che-Yu, the soul fish was born in the void and crystallized from human emotions.

Fluttering silently and slowly, their bodies almost disappeared in the light of the deep sea.
The fish swims freely, and this is the happiness of the fish.
If we are not a fish, how do we know the joy of a fish?
How do we know that we do not know the joy of fish?
We will only learn about it when we come to the riverside.
